<item>
            <title>[ENTESB-5144] AMQP transport provider cannot be set due to TCCL issue </title>
                <link>https://issues.jboss.org/browse/ENTESB-5144</link>
                <project id="12314570" key="ENTESB">JBoss Fuse</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It is not possible to get transport provider in OSGi environment due to TCCL issue now.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/qpid/blob/0.28/qpid/java/amqp-1-0-client/src/main/java/org/apache/qpid/amqp_1_0/client/Connection.java#L267&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/qpid/blob/0.28/qpid/java/amqp-1-0-client/src/main/java/org/apache/qpid/amqp_1_0/client/Connection.java#L267&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I tried to manually modify classloader variable to &lt;tt&gt;getClass().getClassLoader()&lt;/tt&gt; while debugging and then it worked.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It throws &lt;em&gt;&quot;Unknown protocol: amqp&quot;&lt;/em&gt; now.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
